# Scenario 02 — YOLOv5n at 416×416, current active FPS (5 Hz).
#
# Pre-flight (operator, one-time):
#   1. Build the YOLOv5n TRT engine at 416×416. See README.md "Building
#      the YOLOv5n TRT engine" — the resulting file lands at e.g.
#      /home/israel/HomeCameraSystem/detection/models/yolov5n_416.trt.
#   2. The current detect.py call site at line ~725 is:
#         net = jetson_inference.detectNet(model, threshold=DETECT_FLOOR)
#      jetson-inference accepts a model file path as well as a network
#      name string. If you built the engine yourself, point DETECT_MODEL
#      at the file path. If you used `detectnet --network=yolov5n` to
#      let jetson-inference manage it, set DETECT_MODEL=yolov5n.
#   3. There is no DETECT_INPUT_W/H knob today — input size is baked
#      into the engine. If you want 320×320 instead, build a separate
#      engine and swap DETECT_MODEL accordingly.
DETECT_MODEL=yolov5n
DETECT_ACTIVE_FPS=5.0
DETECT_IDLE_FPS=1.0
